        <rows tableBody>
            <row fit pad rounded next=body>
                <?The next attribute above looks up the block named in its text (body), finds its source in that block, gets the next record from that source and assigns it to its parent (thus it sets row.group to the next record block). Also, it creates a hidden sRCe attribute in its parent (row), that contains a pointer to the source (created by the source attribute in the body block)?>
                <firstRow height=16 across border=off>
                    <field tag width=75 tableCell/>
                        <?In the block above, the tag attribute gets the tag of the current source record and stores it in field.text to be displayed. It finds the current source record by looking up the hierarchy for the first sRCe attribute it finds (in this case, in the row block via its next attribute) and accessing the value of the sRCe parent, which is row.group?>
                    <tags source=row useNext useAttributes across=* height=16 scrollWith=contents>
                            <?In the tags block above, how the source works is modified by the useNext and useAttributes attributes. source=row refers to the row block above, which has a sRCe attribute created by next (its next attribute). The sRCe points to the row source, which is listStuff.
                            The useNext attribute modifies the way source works to use the next record (stored in row.group as the source instead of listStuff.
                            The useAttributes attributes modifies the working of any next command that accesses the source (as modified by useNext) so that it gets the next record from the source attributes rather than source members?>
                        <wrap width=75 next=tags>
